<TITLE> Another Kushtia extremist killed in shootout </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kushtia, Aug 29 (bdnews24.com)  A suspected extremist, identified as a top Gono Bahini figure, was killed in a crossfire incident with RAB and police early on Saturday, in the backdrop of deteriorating law and order in the district, law enforcers said. The latest incident is the fourth such death, in shootouts between extremists and law enforcers, in under a week. Saturday's shooting left dead 38-year-old Babul Joaddar, also known as Babul Member, the top local leader of outlawed extremist group Gono Bahini, police said. Babul was the chief associate of Gono Bahini's head Ajibor Rahman, said local police chief Motiar Rahman. The shootout took place near a beel , or water body, in Bamon village near the Islami University in Kushtia's Sadar Upazila, said Rahman, officer-in-charge of Islami University Police Station. A team of RAB 12 and police went to the beel, adjacent to the Bittipara-Patikabari road, at around 4am following a tip-off on a meeting of the outlawed group there, Rahman told bdnews24.com. "The suspects opened fire; RAB and police fired back. The extremists managed to flee the scene and police found the dead body of Babul at the spot." He said a firearm and nine rounds of ammunition were recovered from the spot. The body was sent to Kushtia Sadar Hospital for post mortem. Two suspected extremists were killed in crossfire with police in Kushtia town on Wednesday night. Another Gono Bahini leader Shahinur Rahman Dablu was killed in a shootout Tuesday night, police said. bdn
